Tribal rebels in southwest Pakistan attacked a paramilitary convoy, resulting in three soldiers killed and seven injured.
Violence escalated in Baluchistan after a rocket attack on a gas plant and a doctor's rape near the Sui gasfield.
The Baluchistan Liberation Army claimed responsibility for attacks, leading to fierce gun battles with up to 30 dead.
The exodus from Dera Bugti followed a warning from tribal chief Akbar Bugti.
Clashes left eight soldiers dead, prompting government officials and families to evacuate.
The situation remains tense as armed tribesmen surround troops in Dera Bugti, with fears of renewed fighting.
